45-year-old Bassino blackmailed to death

Iatefa, a lao woman working at a hair salon, told Vientiane

Times the 45-year-old female client was sitting on her mobile phone

for a long time. She said the client’s expression was very

unhappy and she complained about trouble caused by the buyer while

selling goods.

Bassino was attempting to make a payment, she

added, but the buyer insisted on paying via bank transfer, noting

that her mother in the US phoned her and said she had sent money to

an account in Laos. The salon owner told the victim to check for

her.

The victim observed the number of her mobile phones

growing suddenly. According to the victim’s mother, who arrived

in Vientiane yesterday, the victim’s mobile phones were busy with

several or many unknown mobile identity numbers calling her mobile

phone . Bassino tried to call her mother, who told her that the US

and Laos security agencies were monitoring her closely

and Bassino could not disclose her number to her mother.
